<br>
&quot;Good to have you back athelfi.&quot; She grinned and then turned looking at the wolves.<br>
<br>
&quot;Salvage what you can, and leave no man alive!&quot; She rose her daggers in the air and then charged at a fleet of Roman troops that came marching in from the woods. There were only about five of them, and they wore their symbol proudly. It disgusted her.<br>
<br>
Her dagger sunk into the chest of one as two others grabbed her arms pulling her backwards tieing her to a nearby tree. One of the guards came up to strike her but at her sight, his eye's widened.<br>
&quot;General Alysia?&quot; He quirked a brow.<br>
<br>
Alysia grinned darkly. There were always Romans everywhere, but this one happened to have been in her troop when she fought along side Livia many many many years ago.<br>
His pause gave her the opportunity to attack. Though her hands and arms were tied back behind her, she flipped her legs up around his neck, cracking it at the very first chance.<br>
Her fingers reached up behind her tearing at the ropes, and once again, she was free to kill.<br>
<br>
&quot;Gods I love a good blood bath!&quot; <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">~*~ Jessica ~*~<br>
