&quot;Elektra, I see that you are still blood thirsty.&quot; She said quietly. &quot;Any Roman soldier that is not already captured, is yours to torment as you see fit.&quot; <br>
<br>
She turned back to look at the family before her, then at the others that were joining the mother and her children. She noticed that the Roman commander she had was coming too. Cursing and spitting blood out onto the ground as he struggled to his feet. Solari jerked on the rope that held his hands together behind his back, causing him to fall to his knees once more. <br>
<br>
&quot;You witch.&quot; he growled as he sat on his knees. &quot;I will kill you for this.&quot; <br>
<br>
Solari looked down at him, with one swift motion, her boot met with his nose, breaking it and sending him backwards once more into the mud. She heard a gasp of a child, which made her turn back to the families standing there.<br>
&quot;Your families are safe from our wrath. We have gotten what we came for. If you wish sanctuary within our city, join us. If you wish to return to Rome, do so now.&quot; She said in a commanding, but gentle voice. &quot;You are all free now.&quot; <br>
<br>
She jerked the rope once more, sending the Roman forward into the rear of her horse. Laughter from the children erupted as the Roman cursed under his breath. Solari gathered the reins and turned her horse around. She nodded to Elektra to signal that she was leaving and to carry out what ever orders she wished upon the wounded Romans that lay around. As Solari rode out of the village, the Roman tugged on his rope, trying desperatly to hide his face from the stinging mud that was being flung at him by the women and children. The call to return to the encampment was given, and just as quickly as the amazons appeared, they disappeared into the darkness save for a select few remaining in the village to &quot; clean-up. &quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=alexiares>Alexiares</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#993300>(5/8/03 8:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=220>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/queenhippolyte/images/alexiares.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Attack is over</span><hr size=1> Hearing Marpe's orders, Alexiares began to wander near the woods to forage for things they could eat.  One of the things she learned growing up at the temple in Samos was what plants were edible.  As more amazons arrived from the roman village, Alexiares glanced up.  The sight of a couple romans made her bones chill.  <br>
